    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    ApplicantMenu
    Generates a list of actions available to Applicants Depending on the user's selection it will invoke different actions
    changePW
    Allows any user of any user type to change their password
    enquiryInterface
    These methods are related to the enquiry class.
    LoginService
    Login service to allow users to login to access the program functions Generates a login interface that prompts user to enter their username and password username would be their NRIC and default password is password
    Main
    This is our main function that does the following: Read in CSV files Login/Logout function Write back into original CSV files
    ManagerMenu
    Generates a list of actions available to Managers Depending on the user's selection it will invoke different actions
    OfficerMenu
    Generates a list of actions available to Officers Depending on the user's selection it will invoke different actions
    UserPerson
    This class is the superclass to the Manager class and Applicant class, which Officer extends from Stores information on each UserPerson object created from this class Information on each person object: name, NRIC, age, marital status, password and user type Has a method to read from CSV files to get Applicant/Officer/Manager information Gives each user a user type based on which file they are read from Contains methods to get each specific information
